Speaking on Tuesday evening, at a meeting of the Queen’s University Belfast Chief Executives’ Club, Mr Martin complained that previous "genuine" attempts by the EU to make progress on outstanding issues in relation to the protocol were "undermined" by Lord Frost. Mr Martin said: "[Maros Sefcovic] made a very genuine effort and came forward with proposals. I felt Lord Frost at the time probably unfortunately came in on the eve of that to try to, in my view, negatively undermine what was a genuine effort to move forward". Mr Frost’s actions "narrowed the scope of unionist leaders" to respond in a more generous way which led to a "missed opportunity", Mr Martin said. Follow below for live updates...